"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-31-athletes-eating-packed-lunches-olympics-one-food-really-want-21328207\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"For many of us, a packed lunch will likely consist of last night's leftovers, or a sad sandwich andpacket of crisps.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So it might surprise many to hear thatTeam GB's sports starshave been tucking into a 'packed lunch' most nights for dinner at theOlympic VillageinParis.\", \"from\": 118, \"to\": 270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 161, \"end\": 163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999983019766524, \"rank\": 1.5677245809181355e-06, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to Andy Anson, the British Olympic Association's chief executive, the food at the Village has been 'inadequate' meaning that athletes have been getting their meals elsewhere.\", \"from\": 272, \"to\": 456, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 285, \"end\": 295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Anson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andy Anson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Anson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Anson\"}, {\"begin\": 301, \"end\": 328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Olympic Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Andy said a 'dramatic improvement' was needed when it came to food, as there had not been enough protein to go around.\", \"from\": 458, \"to\": 576, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He also claimed thatraw meat had been served to athletes.\", \"from\": 577, \"to\": 634, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of eating at the Village, British athletes have been heading to the Performance Lodge 20 minutes away in Clichy.\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 670, \"end\": 677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9931634570336555, \"rank\": 0.006777699232360235, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 749, \"end\": 755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7073218449894643e-16, \"text\": \"Clichy\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is a space for Team GB where they can train, rest, recover, and prepare for competition.\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 850, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'The athletes are not just going there to eat their lunch, they are packing meals for their dinner as they do not want to go into the athlete restaurant to eat,' Andy adds.\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 1024, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not been revealed what exactly the team have been putting in their lunchboxes, but it's likely they will have been stocking up on everything the village has been in short supply of, including chicken, eggs, and carbohydrates.\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1256, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And some will be eating a hefty amount, as Olympic 200m freestyle champion Tom Dean recently toldThe Independentthat he consumes 6,000 to 7,000 calories per day, with two big breakfasts, a big lunch, a snack, a large meal, and then another snack before bed.\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1333, \"end\": 1341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9999936593363623, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Dean\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His first breakfast typically includes oats with peanut butter, banana, fruits and honey, which gives him around 1,200 calories to begin the day.\", \"from\": 1517, \"to\": 1662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He then follows this up with scrambled eggs, a bagel and avocado.\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1728, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of his fellow British athletes will also be starting their day with porridge, as Philipp W\\u00fcrz, head of food and beverages at the Games, revealed it was the most requested food by Team GB ahead of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1944, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1749, \"end\": 1756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9931634570336555, \"rank\": 0.006777699232360235, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1914, \"end\": 1921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9955338884196312, \"rank\": 0.0044491559010384745, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is likely because it's considered a 'superfood' by many experts.\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 2015, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nigel Mitchell, anutritionistwho has worked with Team GB,previously told Metrothat porridge was his 'number one breakfast choice'.\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2146, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2016, \"end\": 2030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigel_Mitchell\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nigel Mitchell\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigel_Mitchell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigel_Mitchell\"}, {\"begin\": 2065, \"end\": 2072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9955338884196312, \"rank\": 0.0044491559010384745, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'It's warming, comforting and provides ideal slow-release carbohydrates.\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2220, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This helps to maintain blood glucose levels which supports an even brain energy level to prevent drops in mood,' he explained.\", \"from\": 2221, \"to\": 2347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At Metro Food, we are here to bring you all the latest foodie news, delicious recipes, restaurant reviews, and cooking tips.\", \"from\": 2349, \"to\": 2473, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2349, \"end\": 2357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/AT_Metro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"At Metro\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/AT_Metro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/AT_Metro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a loyal reader and a part of our vibrant community, we want to make sure you never miss our articles when searching for stories  Click the button below and tickMetro.co.ukto ensure you see stories from us first in Google Search.\", \"from\": 2474, \"to\": 2705, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2691, \"end\": 2704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Search\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Search\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Search\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Add us as a Preferred Source  From the latest Walkers flavours to the secret McDonald's menu, Metro Food has it all  'I love the versatility of it and it is easy to make it plant-based by swapping the milk for your choice of dairy-free milk.\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2948, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2753, \"end\": 2760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walkers_Limited\", \"score\": 0.9999999999654392, \"rank\": 2.8973001232827107e-11, \"text\": \"Walkers\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walkers_Limited\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walkers_Limited\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I suggest soya because it provides more protein than other dairy-free milk.'\", \"from\": 2949, \"to\": 3025, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When making it yourself, he recommends adding chia seeds for protein and also because they are high in fats which the body uses to make DHA fatty acids.\", \"from\": 3027, \"to\": 3179, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3163, \"end\": 3166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Docosahexaenoic_acid\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3703817905985898e-32, \"text\": \"DHA\", \"types\": [\"Q11173\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Docosahexaenoic_acid\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Docosahexaenoic_acid\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Struggling with thinning or dull hair?\", \"from\": 3181, \"to\": 3219, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Experts say the real issue starts at your scalp  Mother's Day gifts for new mums and mums\\u2011to\\u2011be under \\u00a350  The oral\\u2011care gadget making waves thanks to its powerful clean  Dunelm's new outdoor collection will get your garden spring-ready - from just \\u00a33  The exact blush Margot Robbie wore in Wuthering Heights and best budget alternatives  'This is essential for the brain to function - impacting everything from cognition to mood,' he adds.\", \"from\": 3220, \"to\": 3660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3391, \"end\": 3397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Durham_University\", \"score\": 0.9999999913338797, \"rank\": 8.666144239757224e-09, \"text\": \"Dunelm\", \"types\"